main event: A 16-year-old boy reported tight security around an unidentified object that allegedly landed on a farm near Kansas City, Kansas, on March 29, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as oval or elongated and appeared like a bright star at 20 degrees elevation in the west., The sighting lasted for 5-10 seconds before the object vanished and was said to have returned hours later., The object was stationary during the observation., The observer's report was documented in a Project 10073 Record Card as part of Project Blue Book., The Air Force was unable to confirm the sighting details for another report from Miami, Florida, due to lack of specific information.
sighted object: oval or elongated object resembling a bright star
